  "doc_id": "36462",
  "text": "The recent introduction of commodity depth cameras has led to significant progress in analyzing articulated objects, especially human full-body and hand. In terms of pose estimation, Microsoft Kinect is already widely used in practice at the scale of human full-body, while it is still a research topic at human hand scale [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] 54] , partly due to the dexterous nature of hand articulations. [CITATION_7] is among the first to develop a dedicated convolutional neural net (CNN) method for hand pose estimation, which is followed by [CITATION_8] . [CITATION_9] also utilizes deep learning in a synthesizing-estimation feedback loop.",
